a-size-base: I was worried about these treats when I first took them out of the bag because they're hard like chalk and my dog is 13 years ol
a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2016
a-size-base 3: My Yorkie loves these treats. I was worried about these treats when I first took them out of the bag because they're hard like chalk and my dog is 13 years old. She didn't like them right away but after she started to spend some time on them, they started to dissolve and she could chew on them more easily. These treats are great for distracting dogs but you also have to be careful if they're a smaller dog because the treat is really hard and I could see it could cause choking in over ambitious dogs that don't take the time to break down the treat. The only flaw in these treats is that my dog has a beard and these treats get really milky and foamy and once she finishes her treat it looks like she has rabies and that she's foaming at the mouth. I always find chunks of unfinished twistix dental chews melted to her beard with foam. She loves them so much and they're good for her teeth so I can't complain. I just have to clean her up every time after she's had one of these treats.

I prefer the smell (and her breath) after eating the vanilla mint, but as far as the dog is concerned, she eats both flavors with equal enthusiasm.Original Review...............My dog loves Twistix but twice now, she's thrown up a couple hours after having one at bed time.  We normally give her the vanilla mint version which she's eaten for over a year without any issues.  For some reason, the yogurt banana version doesn't agree with her system.  She weighs 50 lbs and gets only small one at bedtime, so I'm not sure what this issue is with this flavor.  We aren't doing anything differently other than having switched flavors.
